            "text": {
                "headline": "<a href='/class/2017/06/28/version-control/'>Version Control</a>",
                "text": "<p>Version control systems allow us to track and see the changes to a given document or set of files over time. \nThis can be useful in situations where you wish to roll back changes or identify the point of origin for something problematic. </p>\n\n<p>It is also helpful when you are collaborating and want to be able to keep track of the work being done and changes being made by a group of people. </p>\n\n<p>Version control can exist in a standalone system or it can be networked and distributed. </p>"
            },
            "unique_id": "2017-06-28-version-control",
            "group": "class"
               
        },
