            "text": {
                "headline": "<a href='/class/2017/07/12/single-multiple-outputs/'>Single input, multiple outputs</a>",
                "text": "<p>We&#39;ve briefly discussed Pandoc now. \nIt bills itself as the &quot;Universal Document Converter.&quot; \nThis is reasonably true, but it might require some creative combinations of switches within Pandoc commands as well as multiple commands strung together or intermediate commands to get the desired output. </p>\n\n<p>The benefit of troubleshooting and understanding this process is that once we do, we can more easily optimize our conversions and automate them. \nWe&#39;ll talk more about this as we go forward. </p>"
            },
            "unique_id": "2017-07-12-single-input,-multiple-outputs",
            "group": "class"
               
